The paper deals with the convergence to equilibrium of logit dynamics for strategic games, which is a topic in game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the behavior of a complex system and the structure of underlying graphs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of mathematical analysis and proofs indicates that it could also be classified under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
